<h1> ERNAKULAM </h1>  
<p>  
Ernakulam is one of the 14 districts in the Indian state of Kerala, and takes  its name from the eponymous city division in Kochi. It is situated in the  central part of the state, spans an area of about 2,924 square kilometres  (1,129 sq mi), and is home to over 9% of Kerala's population. Its  headquarters are located at Kakkanad. The district includes Kochi, also  known as the commercial capital of Kerala, which is famous for its ancient  churches, Hindu temples, synagogues  
</p>  
